description:
&lt;p&gt;We require an experienced and enthusiastic Locum Consultant Uro-Radiologist to join our team of 23 Consultant Radiologists. The appointee will be based at Eastbourne DGH although this may change dependent on service need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should demonstrate a high level of clinical experience and competence in Genitourinary Radiology across all major modalities. Experience in multi-parametric prostate MRI is favourable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;East Sussex Healthcare (ESHT) offers comprehensive and state-of-the-art management of urological diseases and is a major tertiary referral centre for the management of Urological Cancers, Stone Disease and Female/Functional Urology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ESHT Radiology Department has a high quality stock of imaging Equipment including a 320 slice Toshiba Aquilion One, GE Revolution and Evolution CT machines, 2x MRI Siemens Avanto 1.5T, Siemens Artis Interventional Suite, Siemens Symbiat 16 SPECT-CT and an ongoing rolling equipment replacement and expansion programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First line on call is provided by SpR or staff grade radiologists until 10pm weekdays and 5pm weekends with on call outsourced to a reporting company overnight. Our General Radiology consultant team is responsible for checking SpR scans the following day to ensure quality assurance and education on a 1 in 8 rota. This rota also covers Malignant cord compression MRI at weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Radiology Departments are actively involved in teaching with four radiology trainees on rotation from HEKSS deanery. Audit and other continuing professional developmental activities are positively encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will be offered on the Terms and Conditions in line with national pay scales. Applicants must have full GMC registration with a licence to practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Justin Harris-Deputy Chief of Division (Diagnostics, Anesthetics and Surgery)Telephone number0300 131 4843&lt;/p&gt;
